<br>
When it comes to how much aaxp you get, consider it mathematically.<br>
Say a 24k hp mob is worth 9% aaxp per kill before split(24,000hp = 9%aaxp) and you have 120dps. 24,000/120 = 9% aaxp per 200 sec, or 162% aaxp per hour is your value. Now, generally people regard aaxp in terms of how much experience they get per hour. Since aaxp can be converted to correspond with a mob's hp by its aaxp per kill, then your dps can be converted into aaxp/s as demonstrated here. Merely taking this over a longer period of time to relate all of the damage done in an hour (432,000 at 120dps sustained) will probably support your point of that the amount of damage you do over a long period of time is more signifiance than burst dps.<br>
